Soviet Concentional Contacts:
ALMIDATF made the following comments concerning what appeared to
hor to be cormctional contacts and/or notias operandi of Soviet Intel-
ligance cilibria in 'Munico:
Detriefting conducted 23-26 April 1970:
LOGIIOV - During the affair between AENIDRIFF and LOGIIOV,
they went to the movies once or twice a week, the Futurana and Cine Mod
being the theaters most frequently attended. LOGIIOV always trade some
sort of contact during these outings, according to AEMIDRIFF. She stated
that he usually left his seat about 2300 hours and went out to the lobby
for some time. She did not know where the contacts were actually made.
Once she and LOGIIOV encountered, apparently accidentally, outside the
Cine Mod theater, a Mexican Army Colonel, who was introduced to her by
LOGIIOV is "Col. Sergio." In this instance LOGIIOV did not excuse himself
to have a private conversation with the Mexican. "Col. Sergio" was de-
scribed by AMIDIRIFF as about 40, tall, no moustache or glasses, thick,
curly hair, appeared to be of Spanish descent. The vocan with "Col.
Sergio" appeared to be about 25 years old and was introduced as his wife
(which AMIDIRIFF doubted because, as she put it, he didn't treet her as
one would a wife, but rather as a nistress). AMIDIRIFF knew nothing more
about this Mexican and never saw his again.
On another occasion, LOGIIOV and AMIDIRIFF met an American in
front of the Futurana theater. LOGIIOV introduced him to her as "Col.
Michael." AMIDIRIFY stated that he was dressed in civilian clothes. He

Concerning Soviet Contacts in the Nexien Folice: AMTIBRIFF
stated that she overheard GOLCUSSV and DUCMIN talk about many contacts which
they had in the police here. Sin said she had also overhead HOLCKWAXOY,
BARCLINI, AND CEMKIOV talk about how many good police contacts the Soviets
have. However, each specific example which AMTIBRIFF could give concerned

when the Soviets wanted to get something through Aduans; when some Soviet
was missing and police cooperation was needed; getting advance notice when
some demonstration hostile' to the Soviets was about to take place, etc.
She was not able to recall any hints that Soviets had operational contacts
in the police; agents reporting on what the police were doing; assets who
assisted Soviets operationally in scee way. However, AMTIBRIFF thought
the Soviets probably have such assets.

Notes from the Debriefing of AMIDRIFF - 20 to 23 February 1970
1969
19) Valentin Sorcevecvich LACTION: He left on the 6th of nctober for
"oscon, six ronths before the completion of his tour. He was head
of the consular section and the lover of naya, "apparently the
causes for his sudden return were 1) having been naya's lover; and 2)
not having had good results from his work and, according to Naya,
sore kind of failure. He was in "exico on two different occasions.
She states that during the time she was having an affair with Valentin
LORINOY, who was chief of the consular section, he occasionally took
her out at night to places where she knows he rade contact with persons
who scored to the 'exicans. She says that she doesn't know with which
persons he made contact, nor if they were "exicans or not, because she
never sar then, hut that he, on several occasions took her to these
places: the (ine "od on know Lomas de Tecomachalco, the (ine Futurana
in Colonia lindavista, the drive-in tienter called 'autocinema del valle,
the drive-in called Autocinem Satelite and the fine Tlatelolco. When
she accompanied him to those places, he left the car and she remained
in it; that he vould no for 10, 15 or. 20 minutes to converse with those
people. He never told her the these persons were nor what they talked
about.

ARRESTED FOR ESPIONAGE (ALEXANDER V. TIANCIRUVO). MET HIM IN
NOSCOW WHEN HE VAS STUDYING AT INSTITUTES OF FOREIGN RELATIONS. AT
THIS TIME SHE WORKING FOR MINISTRY OF FOREIGN TRADE, IN ADJACENT
EULIDING. TIANCHIROV HAD REPUTATION OF BEINS ONE OF BEST
TRANSLATORS OF HIS TIME.
200
4. SUBJECT EARNS 2500 PESOS (TIP USD) PER MONTH PLUS
SHALL QUANTITY RULES DEPOSITED IN MOSCOW. STATED SHE NEVER HAD
OR HOLDS ON TO NONEY SECAUSE SHE ALWAYS LIKED TO BUY NICE THINGS.
5. EVER SINCE ARRIVAL IN MEXICO SUBJECT HAS BEEN REPRINANDED
FOR HER TASTES WHICH VEPE "OUTSIDE ERBASSY WORN", AEOUS ALL IN
NORAL QUESTIONS, BUT ALSO FOR DYING HER HAIR, WEARING PANTS,
AND NOT BUYING SAME CLOTHES ENBASSY WIVES USUALLY BOUGHT. SHE
HAD FOLLOWING "NORAL" PROBLEMS:
A. SHE WAS MISTRESS OF FORHER HEAD OF CONSULAR SECTION
(VALLEITIN LCGINOV) WHO WAS SENT HOME WHEN THEIR RELATIONSHIP
DISCOVERED. SHE HERSELF HAS PRODUCED EVEN THOUGH THEY
FIRST SAID SHE WOULD RETURN WITH LOSINOV.

UNRENA FOR WEEKEND. WHEN NER ASSENCE DISCOVERED ON 14
DECANIER SOVIETS LOOKED ALL OVER MEXICO CITY AND EVEN ASKED
SECRET

HE IGNORED HER. ON 7 FEBRUARY SHE AGAIN ASZED URUENA FOR HELP,
SAYING IF HE DID NOT THERE WAS NO WAY OUT-- EITHER SAE RETURNED
TO SOVIET UNION AND SUFFENED CONSEQUENCES, OR SHE CONBITTED SUICIDE
IN MEXICO. URUEUA TNE: INTRODUCED HEK TO ONE RICARDO FIERIO, WHO
HID HER FOR TWO DAYS. (STATION COMMENT: THIS VERSION OF SEQUENCE
OF EVENTS APPEARS SOMEWHAT CARBLED. ADDITIONAL DETAIL RE ACTUAL
ESCAPE CANE IN CONVERSATION WITH FLUTEO JHERN SUBJECT SAID SHE HAD
RECEIVED PERMISSION TO GO TO FANENELL PARTY 7 FEBRUARY. PARTY
WAS IN APARTMENT IN WHICH SHE YOOK AUFUSE.)
8. SINCE DEFECTION SUBJECT HAS BEEN TRYING TO FIND URUENA,
WHO WAS DUE TO RETURN FROM BOUTERARY, THERE HE RAD GOUE OR 8
FEBRUARY. RICARDO FICARO HAS ELEN GO-ESTIEN, AND HE REPORTED ON
11 FEBRUARY, THAT "DUE TO THE SITUATION." URUENA COULD NOT NOVE.
9. URUENA'S SISTER BARI, UNO OFORIS FOR MABALINE "GENTE,"
CALLED SUBJECT INHIN SHE LEANED or. EUGO EXFLOSION ACROSS STARET
FROH CONNERCIAL OFFICE (CASE MILD RESULTED 11 FIRST RENOWAL OF
L ITEMPO-12 PER PARA 1 WEICO CITY 2444). RARI KUEW THAT RAN WHO
NO SEEN KILLED WAS CLOSE FALLEN OF RARE LISSTON CRUFFUR
DANILL HONTIEL CHRO HAS WORLD FO. : ESTION FOR 15 YEARS.

PAGE 6 NEXICO CITY 2472 S E C R E T
18. CONFRONTATION OF SUBJECT IN GOVERNACION WAS ATTENDED
BY OLEG NECHIPORENKO, CHARGE BONIS KAZANISEV, AND ONE OTHER SOVIET
IDENTITY NOT CLEARO. SUBJECT STATED ALL THREE SPOKE TO HER
NICELY, SAYING THAT IF SHE NEEDED ANYTHING SUCH AS MOHEY OR CLOTHING,
THEY WOULD SEND IT TO HER. THEY WERE HER FRIENDS AND WERE ONLY
TRYING TO HELP HER. BUT AT END OF INTERVEY WHEN SHE SAID THAT
SHE WAS REMAINING IN MEXICO AND IT WAS BETTER THAT THEY FORGOT
ABOUT HER, KAZANISEV TOLD HER THAT "THE LONGER SHE STAYED THE WORSE
IT WOULD BE FOR HER WHEN SHE RETURNED."

MIAO
REDETOP/HICRUSH
Assessment of AEDIRARD
REVERKACES: A. HINHA 37833, 12 September 1969
B. TGA 3500, 10 October 1969
1. The two Personality Assessment Questionnaires on AEDIRHARD
which were transmitted as separate cover attachments to Reference
A vero unfortunately not received until 30 September, by which
date we knew from a vina cable sent the State Department by the
Embassy in Boryo City that ADDIEMARD was departing PCS one week
therefore, the U.S. Department of Rececece B confirmed that departure.
2. Since but one week was available for the completion of
the HICRUSH assessment, and its transmittal to the Station, we
decided not to go ahead with it. The PAQ's have been made a part
of AEDIRHARD's file, and should be appear in the future outside
the USSR, an assessment can be made at that time.
Norma W. LETCHWORTH
Distribution:
3-COS, Mexico City

Chief, WH Division
(AR AROU) MENTIONS
FROM
Chief of Station, Mexico City
A
AMERICAN
TOUR
HARDTOD' AKICK
Vallent in Sergevevich LOGJNOV (231-285412)
AMERICAN
AMERICAN
Subject, accompanied by his wife, Aleksandron Dmitriyevna,
and son, Dmitriy, departed Mexico City PCS on 7 October 1969. They
travelled to New York via Air France flight 700. From New York
they would fly Aeraflot to Moscow.
2. Subject and his wife were honored by several going-away
parties, one of which was given on 1 October at the Sovie t Embuasy.
3. Subject stated several times before he left that he hoped
that he would return to Mexico and said that there was a good
chance he would come back.
4. Subject introduced Oleg Maksimovich NECHIPORLENKO (201-305870)
as his replacement as Chief of the Consular Office of the Soviet
Embussy. Subject replaced NECHIPORLENKO as Vice-Consul when ho
arrived PCS in August 1965.
5. We do not have any information as yet as to the arrival
of Anatoly Sergeyevich LAZURIN (201-
), who according to
DIRECTOR 27630, 7 August 1969, is scheduled to replace LOGINOV.
6. Forwarded herewith is transit visa information as well as
copies of the passports used by Subject and his wife.
Please A
for/John A. PROBERT
Attachment:
Passport and visa h/w

OCT 23 1969

 THE
 DE
 DE DE DE                                     
	



542
(13) On 12 December 1968 two team members spotted Valentin
S. LOGINOV (known KGB) walking with an unknown Mexican male.
After LOGINOV departed the Mexican remained at a restaurant
for an hour appearing to be waiting for someone. The Mexican
finally departed after making a phone call and was lost in
heavy traffic. The team members obtained the Mexican's license
plate number from which he was identified as Ignacio VALLINA
Barros.
From notes for Cos Conference, 24-28 March 1969
26.285412
